  <div class="task-title">6. Configure chrony</div>
  Configure chrony such that time is synchronized with <b>"clone-server"</b> i.e., NTP server.
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q7"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q7"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">7. Configure autofs</div>
  Create <b>user1</b> with uid <b>4001</b>, using <b>/rhome</b> as a base directory but do not creat home directory. Make sure the share <b>clone-server-or-ip:/remoteusers/user1</b> should be mounted on <b>/rhome/user1</b>.
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q8"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q8"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">8. Configure Autofs</div>
  Automatically mount the NFS shares <b>nfs-server:/public</b> and <b>nfs-server:/private</b> on <b>/automount</b>.
  <ul>
    <li>The public share should be <b>read-only</b> for all users.</li>
    <li>The private share should be <b>read-write</b> for all users.</li>
    <li>Both shares should automatically unmount.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q9"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q9"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">9. Troubleshoot webserver</div>
  If successfully running, the webserver should show <b>"I am enjoying RHCSA preparation"</b> on port <b>82</b> without changing any configuration.
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q10"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q10"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">10. Collaboration Directory</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Create directory <b>/project</b></li>
    <li>Full access to user and group, no access for others.</li>
    <li>New files inherit group ownership <b>developers</b>.</li>
    <li>Users cannot delete other user files.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q11"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q11"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">11. User & Group Tasks</div>
  Perform the following tasks:
  <ul>
    <li>Create group named <b>admins</b>.</li>
    <li>create users <b>max</b>, <b>bob</b>, and <b>chris</b>.</li>
    <li>Add max and bob as secondary members of <b>admins</b> group.</li>
    <li>Ensure that <b>chris</b> does not have login shell and is not added to the <b>admins</b> group.</li>
    <li>Configure passwordless sudo access for all members of the <b>admins</b> group so they can execute administrative commands without being prompted for a password.</li>
    <li>Modify the umask for user <b>bob</b> so that all newly created files have the permissions where the user and group have read and write, and others have read-only access.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q12"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q12"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">12. Password Expiration</div>
  To ensure security for user <b>max</b> perform following tasks:
  <ul>
    <li>Force user <b>max</b> to change his password at first login.</li>
    <li>Set an account expiration period of <b>45 days</b> for the user <b>max</b>.</li> 
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
